[[Image:Valpayattu.jpg|right|250px|thumb|An [[Ankam]] by Ankachekavars.]]

'''Ankachekavar''' is a word in the [[Malayalam]] language for 'a person fighting for his ruler'. A few centuries back in [[Kerala]], [[south India]], quarrels between local rulers were resolved by fixing an ''Ankam'', a duel to the death, between two ''Ankachekavar''s, each ruler being represented by one ''Ankachekavar''. The ruler represented by the surviving ''Ankachekavar'' was considered the winner.

